# [src/services/SmartSmsProcessor.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/expensetracker/mobile/src/services/SmartSmsProcessor.ts) - Technical Explanation

This is the central "Brain" service. It connects the background SMS listener to the Regex Engine, evaluates spam, tracks merchant renaming records, and commits final parsed outputs to the SQLite database.

## 1. Spam Filtering & Validation (Lines 39-138)
```typescript
const BANK_INDICATORS = [ /debited|credited|spent/, /A\/c|account/, /UPI|IMPS/ ];
const BANK_SENDER_IDS = [ /HDFCBK/, /SBIN/, /ICICIB/ ];
const SPAM_INDICATORS = [ /click here/, /win|won/, /\d{4,8}\s+is\s+your\s+OTP/ ];

export async function validateTransactionSms(sms: string, sender: string): Promise<SmsValidationResult> {
    let confidence = 0;
    if (/-[P]($|[A-Z])/i.test(sender)) return { isValid: false }; // Block Promotional
    if (spamMatches > 0) return { isValid: false };

    // Point system evaluating sender legitimacy + keyword density
    if (bankMatches >= 2) confidence += 0.7;
    
    return { isValid: confidence >= 0.6, ... };
}
```
*   **Logical Flow**: 
    1. Instantly blocks any sender ending in `-P` (telecom standard for Promotional messages).
    2. Instantly blocks messages containing URLs or OTP codes.
    3. Uses a calculated 'Confidence Score'. HDFC Bank + "debited" = 1.0 (Pass). Unknown Sender + "debited" = 0.3 (Fail). Unknown Sender + "debited" + "A/c" + "Rs. 50" = 0.8 (Pass).

## 2. Managing Merchant Naming Rules (Lines 158-222)
```typescript
export async function saveMerchantName(...) {
    // 1. Save rule to database
    await insertMerchantMapping({ smsName: rawName.toUpperCase(), displayName, ... });

    // 2. Loop back and fix past errors
    await updateAllTransactionsForMerchant(rawName, displayName, categoryId);
    
    // 3. Command UI to rebuild
    DeviceEventEmitter.emit('TRANSACTION_UPDATED');
}
```
*   **Logical Flow**: When a user renames `TXN*BBSK` to "BigBasket", this function executes that rule. Crucially, it triggers the [updateAllTransactionsForMerchant](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/expensetracker/mobile/src/services/SmartSmsProcessor.ts#194-223) SQL query to retroactively scan the database and rename any older, historically ugly transactions to match the new naming scheme instantly.

## 3. Account Auto-Creation Module (Lines 409-483)
```typescript
async function resolveAccountId(last4: string | undefined, sender: string, userId: number) {
    // ... Check if account exists
    const [existing] = await db.executeSql(
         'SELECT id FROM accounts WHERE bank_name = ? AND last_4 = ?', [bankName, last4]
    );

    // ... Create if missing
    const defaultName = `${bankName} debit - ${last4}`;
    const [result] = await db.executeSql(
         'INSERT INTO accounts (name, bank_name, last_4...) VALUES (...)', ...
    );
}
```
*   **Logical Flow**: If an SMS arrives from "HDFC" for an account ending in "1122", it checks if the app tracks that account. If it doesn't, it silently creates a new digital wallet in the database named "HDFC debit - 1122" on the fly so the transaction has a valid `account_id` relationship to link to.

## 4. The Master Process Flow ([processSmartSms](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/expensetracker/mobile/src/services/SmartSmsProcessor.ts#260-407)) (Lines 260-406)
```typescript
export async function processSmartSms(sms: string, sender: string, ...) {
    // 1. Safety Gate
    if (!currentUserId) return { success: false };
    
    // 2. Anti-Spam Gate
    const validation = await validateTransactionSms(sms, sender);
    if (!validation.isValid) return { success: false };

    // 3. Text Extraction
    const parsed = await parseExpense(sms, ...);

    // 4. Memory Check (Have we seen this merchant before?)
    const mapping = await getMerchantMapping(parsed.merchant, currentUserId);
    
    let displayName = mapping ? mapping.displayName : parsed.merchant;

    // 5. Hard Save
    const transactionId = await insertTransaction({ amount: parsed.amount, merchant: displayName, ... });

    // 6. UI Prompt Gate
    if (!mapping) {
        if (onNewMerchantCallback) onNewMerchantCallback({...});
    }
}
```
*   **Logical Flow**: The central orchestrator. It receives raw background pushes, feeds them through validation algorithms, extracts the data, applies customized user rules, saves it to SQLite, and formally opens the popup asking the user to rename it if it's completely foreign.
